<recipe 
xmlns="https://cazzscookingcommunity.github.io" 
xmlns:xsi="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema-instance" 
xsi:schemaLocation="https://cazzscookingcommunity.github.io /xml/recipe.xsd"> 
                                                                                
    <title>Buckwheat Pancakes</title>
    <filename>buckwheat_pancakes.xml</filename>

    <comment>c/o McKenzies</comment>
    <thumbnail>../images/placeholder.png</thumbnail>
    <image></image>
    <category></category>
    <yield></yield>
    <prepTime></prepTime>
    <cookTime></cookTime>
    


    <diet>GlutenFree</diet>


    <ingredient>1 1/2 cups buckwheat flour (McKenzies if possible)</ingredient>
    <ingredient>2 tsp baking powder</ingredient>
    <ingredient>1 cup milk</ingredient>
    <ingredient>2 large eggs beaten</ingredient>
    <ingredient>2 TBsp honey or maple syrup </ingredient>
    <ingredient>Butter for the pan </ingredient>
    <ingredient>Desired toppings</ingredient>

    <step>
Mix dry ingredients together and in a separate bowl mix wet ingredients. Combine together and mix until lumps removed. Melt butter in pan. Pour 2 TBsp amounts into medium hot pan and cook until bubbles pop in the batter. Flip over and cook until golden brown. Cook until all done and serve with favourite toppings.
    </step>
</recipe>